===Etymology===
Latin, "the thing speaks for itself."
===Legal maxim===
#A [[maxim]] where the very improbable facts of an accident imply the [[negligence]] of the defendant.  It effectively shifts the [[burden of proof]] to the [[defendant]]. 
===References===
The doctrine was invoked in the English case ''Byrne v. Boadle'' (1863) 2 [[H. & C.]] 722, which involved a barrel of flour falling from a storehouse window onto a pedestrian. Sometimes shortened to ''res ipsa'', or ''resipsy.''
